I have starred at the screen for two hours on Friday for an easy question...

Take the limit of $p_n$:
\begin{gather*}
\lim_{n \to \infty} p_n = 
	a\lim_{n \to \infty} 7^{n}
		+ b\lim_{n \to \infty} \frac{1}{7^n}\\
= a\lim_{n \to \infty} 7^{n} + 0
\end{gather*}
But $a = \frac{1}{48}(7(\frac{1}{7}) - 1) = 0$.
Hence the limit goes to zero.
Therefore, the given computation is stable.
\hfill $\blacksquare$
